// Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) Data Science model deployment
//
// Examine a single model deployment — a model from the catalog served
// as an HTTP inference endpoint. Select a deployment by its OCID, for
// example
// `oci.ai.dataScience.modelDeployment(id: "ocid1.datasciencemodeldeployment.oc1...")`.
// The deployment reports its endpoint URL, its instance and model
// configuration, and the access and predict logging attached to it.
private oci.ai.dataScience.modelDeployment @defaults("name state") {
  init(id? string)
  // Model deployment OCID
  id string
  // Model deployment display name
  name string
  // Compartment OCID containing the deployment
  compartmentID string
  // Compartment containing the deployment
  compartment() oci.compartment
  // OCID of the project the deployment belongs to
  projectID string
  // Project the deployment belongs to
  project() oci.ai.dataScience.project
  // OCID of the principal that created the deployment
  createdBy string
  // Description of the deployment
  description string
  // URL of the inference endpoint
  modelDeploymentUrl string
  // Instance and model configuration of the deployment
  //
  // Includes the deployment type and, for a single-model deployment, the
  // model OCID, instance shape, instance count, and bandwidth.
  configuration dict
  // Access and predict logging attached to the deployment
  //
  // Has `access` and `predict`, each with the OCID of the log and log
  // group when logging is enabled.
  loggingConfiguration dict
  // Lifecycle state (e.g., CREATING, ACTIVE, DELETING, DELETED, FAILED, INACTIVE, UPDATING, NEEDS_ATTENTION)
  state string
  // Creation time
  created time
  // Free-form tags for resource management
  freeformTags map[string]string
  // Defined tags for governance and cost tracking
  definedTags map[string]map[string]string
}

